<font color="#FF0000">RESPECT</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 10 19:40:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I have just stumbled upon this when I was doing research on the topic of PTSD and Vietnam Veterans and I have to say my heart goes out to all of you who had the courage to serve our country in such a place. I have the utmost respect for all you men and women out there. My father was in Nam and he used to tell some pretty bad stuff that he experienced. If it wasn't for all of those who died, then my father might not have come back. I know he still thinks about it. Fourth of July's still bother him to this day. I also am a veteran who served this country and even though I was afraid of some of the things we were sent to do, I knew that as a soldier, It was my duty to my country to hang in there no matter what, even though my tour was in a much calmer time. All of you are true Americans and If I could shake all of your hands and say thank you for serving and for helping bring my father back, I would. But I am afraid that this will have to do. Again, Thank You   
<p><code>--   (Mike) </code><p>


